nodes.bodyText:
@awalther28 is the INNER JOIN critical to the short answer for detecting anomalies?  Is it possible that only the WINDOWING is the key piece of the solution?  (In that, INNER JOIN is only required if the data isn't already joined...).
Two benefits to consider if INNER JOIN were removed are (a) keeping the short answer short and (b) freeing up real estate on the site.
I'm on the fence, just wanted to share this food for thought
